name: Coffee Perk
directions: Near the door, to the right of the counter.
comment: Mon-Fri 7AM to 10:30PMSat-Sun 8AM to 10:30PM

name: Portland Public Library
directions: Located on the bottom floor.

name: Shaw's Supermarket
directions: Located next to Customer Service.
comment: 2 single person, genderfree bathrooms open to public. Hand ralls are there if needed. Doors are wide enough for wheelchair entrance. Open early morning - late night (maybe 6 am -11 pm?)

name: Masterpiece Massage
directions: Gender Neutral restrooms are clean and accessible.  Lots of free parking.
comment: If you have time please say hello to Kelly Vickers and/& Karla Linden.  This is a safe place.

name: MasterPeace Mediation
directions: Two gender neutral bathrooms are in the center of the building.  Plenty of free parking.
comment: If you have time please say hello to Kelly Vickers, JD and/or Karla Linden, LMT.  This is a safe place for all.

name: Sears
directions: Located between the tools/electronics section and the Auto Center.
comment: This is signed as a family room/handicap restroom. It is single room with a locking door.

name: Samena Swim Club
directions: From entrance, head straight until you reach the key checkin. There is a Unisex bathroom on the right, and in the furthest hallway on the left two family (unisex) bathroom and shower combos.
comment: Ask the desk person if you could 'use the restroom real fast', it's a family friendly club so should be accomodating.

name: Kohls
directions: Walk into the store from the Entrance on Baseline road, it's on the right wall of the store, half way down (in the same little outlet as customer service).

name: Galleria Mall Henderson NV
directions: Go to food court. The family restroom is between the mens and ladies room

name: Cinemark 19
street: 1030 W Grand Pkwy N, Katy, TX‎
comment: Gender neutral, ADA accessible restroom found near the east front exit.

name: The Hobby Center for the Performing Arts‎
comment: My girlfriend and I went there for a musical and found gender neutral single occupancy restrooms in between gendered restrooms in most floors. They were mostly empty even during intermission.

name: hancocks
directions: walk straight to back, toilet on right.don't go in unauthorized zone!!
comment: not only will you feel safe while peeing, but you can also find lots of good treats!

name: Toss Across
directions: In the back on the left-hand side... just around the corner from where you order food.
comment: They are open 11 to 8 pm, Monday through Saturday and noon to 5pm on Sundays

name: Public Restaurant
directions: Enter restaurant, walk down half flight of stairs to the bar. Two single occupancy restrooms marked UNISEX are at the end of the bar.

name: Equal Grounds
directions: Walk through to the back of the shop.  Between the bookcases there's a door, which says, 'Restroom for customer use only.'  Go through that door; the bathroom is on the other side.
comment: Great LGBT coffee shop.  Make sure you support it when you use their bathroom :)

name: Liquid Planet
directions: There are two gender-neutral bathrooms in the way back.
comment: Clean!

name: Bourbon Coffee
comment: The staff often tell people that it's okay to use either restroom. They're effectively gender free, but I've been told they're gendered because Cambridge law requires such. also, the coffee is good

name: Cool Moose Cafe
directions: Walk in on the entrance on the left and straight ahead.
comment: Single Stall

name: fhs
directions: =cozy facilities=

name: Dyanna Body & Nail Salon-Spa:Brazilian Waxing:Hair Removal:Electrolysis:New York‎
comment: You can pee before or after waxing.

name: starbucks
directions: behind the counter
comment: you need the door code, so you should buy something

name: Ross Cherry Creek Library
directions: Second floor, past the public computer area, past the meeting rooms, in the corner.

name: Mission Viejo Library
directions: Check out some books, DVDs, or CDs when you're done.
comment: Monday - Thursday: 10 a.m. to 9 p.m.Friday: 1 p.m. to 5 p.m.Saturday: 10 a.m. to 5 p.m.Sunday: 12 p.m. to 5 p.m.

name: Casa Nueva
directions: When you walk in, you are in the Cantina/Bar - restrooms are in rear left of room along the hallway under the exit sign where the community bulletin board is located.
comment: Family friendly establishment.After 10pm - may be a cover charge to enter, mainly on weekends.Additional bathrooms are in restaurant which closes at 10pm, and are single stall preferred for restaurant customers only.

name: Marche Artisan Foods
directions: Right near the check out register toward the right.

name: University of Colorado @ Colorado Springs
directions: Located on 1st, 2nd, 3rd, and 4th floors of Columbine Hall in the office wings
comment: Gender nuetral/ Unisex bathrooms-single stall-locking- More to come!

name: University of Florida - Florida Gymnasium
directions: FLG is east of the Stadium. Take the east entrance near the bike parking from the infirmary side. Take the stairs (on the left as you enter) up to first floor inside, take the first left out the stairs and mens bathroom is immediately right there. Womens? must be on the same floor...
comment: Ultimate private single stall wheelchair friendly spacious bathroom. Well worth the bike ride. Lighted, clean, sink with mirror, liquid soap, TP, garbage can, and usually the alligator inside! Unfortunately, not open late. Hands down the best bathroom on campus otherwise

name: Gaia House Interfaith Center
directions: The upstairs bathrooms are gendered but the downstairs bathroom is genderfree, single occupant, and lockable.
comment: Our official hours for Spring 2012 are only 11 am to 3 pm. However, we're usually open later than 3 pm and hope to expand our hours in the Fall. We're also often open to the public during events, especially Thursday and Friday nights.

name: Lawrence University - Warch Campus Center
directions: There are two on the 4th floor (one floor up from entry level)
comment: Campus center is open 24 hours a  day while school is in session (students have key-card access w/ LU ID after midnight).

name: Bellingham
directions: On The corner around from the bead store
comment: Private and single... 2 different Bathrooms

name: Smith College, Burton Hall
directions: The bathrooms on the second and third floors are still vaguely labeled 'M' and 'W', but really they're gender-neutral.  Everyone uses both.
comment: Burton is a science/math building and is unlocked during the day time.

name: Chipotle Mexican Restaurant
directions: It's to the left of the counter and the line when you come in.
comment: Open 11AM to 10 PM.If it's busy, no one will even notice if you come in to use the bathroom and leave.  Otherwise, just buy a drink.

name: Chipotle
directions: When you enter, you're in line, but if you go off to the right and bypass the line and the counter you'll be in the eating area.  Bathrooms are on the left wall if you're standing in the center of the room facing the same direction as the counter.
comment: I don't think they'd really care if you just slid in to use the restroom, especially if it's busy.  Buy a drink if you're worried.

name: Starbucks
directions: Restrooms in the back of the building, past the counter.
comment: Hours6AM to 10 PM Monday-Saturday7AM to 10 PM SundayI don't think they really care if you buy something, especially if it's busy.  If it's really slow they might be a more observant of who's going in/out.

name: Giant Eagle Supermarket
directions: Go in through the sliding doors and they're directly to the right after you get inside the building.
comment: Hours7AM-11PM Monday through Saturday7AM-9PM SundayCloses early some holidays.

name: In Other Words Feminist Community Center
directions: In the front door and to the left.

name: Bike Forth
directions: corner of 4th and L
comment: see website for latest hours:  davisbikecollective.org

name: AJ Java East gone
comment: no longer at this location

name: Thai Delight
directions: in the back, past the kitchen, on the right.
comment: One single stall, locking door bathroom for everybody.

name: local 123
directions: There are two gender-free bathrroms in the back, to the left.
comment: Genderqueer/Trans friendly owners and workers.

name: Yale School of Medicine
comment: Single stall restroom outside of library on first floor is marked male/female. Yale ID is required for entry to building but security guards don't check if you look \"Yale enough.\"

name: Firefly Restaurant
directions: 1st floor, hallway at back right of restaurant
comment: Attached to Hotel Madera, GLBTQ friendly

name: Boise State University Student Union Building
directions: Second floor of the student union building (next to the soccer field), right off university drive just before you get to lincoln avenue.
comment: Opens at 6:00 on weekdays, 7:00 on weekends.Closes at 24:00 during semesters and at 23:00 during breaks between semesters.Unisex restroom, should be accessible (marked that way) but pretty small on the inside and certainly not perfect accessability-wise. Lockable, single toilet. Cleaned twice a day.

name: Oberlin College, Peters Hall
directions: The building on the middle block of campus that kind of looks like a castle. Fourth floor (there's an elevator), outside the language library/lab. All-gender, single stall.
comment: Peters is the language/observatory building. Less convenient than Mudd or Student Union (Wilder), but it's there.

name: Octane Coffee
comment: Bathrooms are single-seat and lightly gendered; when I suggested degendering them to the staff, they said with a smile that most people just take the initiative to use whatever bathroom they like, whether because of a line or because of their gender identity.

name: Southwest Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: located on main level of sanctuary.  Right now it is not accessible to Wheelchairs, but renovations will begin in May 2010.  An elevator will be added to the building
comment: We are a welcoming congregation.  We even know how to use gender neutral pronouns!

name: East Hall, 3rd Floor
directions: West side of Church street, just north of South University.
comment: Social psych department

name: Good Foods Market & Cafe
directions: In the Cafe
comment: Beatifully renovated from 2 single non-gender rooms to 2 gendered big bathrooms in 2009.  Now have 2 women's stalls and 2 men's stalls with a urinal.  Both bathrooms have Dyson hand-dryers, which save electricity and paper waste.  Bathrooms are in the Cafe so you can walk right in.  Clean with automatic faucets and biodegradable handsoap. The Co-op made a commitment to use recycled and \"green\" materials.

name: Rackham Graduate School
directions: 3rd Floor, east side of building.
comment: Building is open from 8 to 9, Monday through Friday.Recently converted from gendered to genderfree.

name: Riverwind Casino
street: I-35 and west hwy 9 - Norman, OK
directions: family bathroom is on the left side of the theatre entrance inside the casino - map directions at http://www.riverwindcasino.com/Map.aspx

name: Coffee Talk
directions: Two single stall gendered bathrooms at the back of the coffee shop.
comment: The two restrooms are technically gendered but the signs are not very obvious and are in a bit of a enclave so you shouldn't have a problem going where you please.

name: Shokudo Japanese Restaurant & Bar
directions: This bathroom is inside the restaurant.  It\\'s probably best you dine here too, but you can feel rest assured that there\\'s a single stall, accessible, genderfree, clean bathroom in the back.

name: Dunkin Donuts
street: SE 15th and Sunnylane Rd, Del City, OK
directions: 1 mile south of I-40 on Sunnylane Rd
comment: restroom is non-gendered

name: Bedford Square
directions: There are two all-gender bathrooms in Bedford Square: one on the first floor, and one in the basement.  The building is accessible by stairs or a ramp and there is a freight elevator to reach the basement.
comment: This building is unlocked during normal business hours (M-F, 9AM to 5PM).  It houses a variety of holistic health professionals and the Gay Straight Alliance for Safe Schools (GSAFE).

name: IMU, 3rd floor
directions: It's right down the hall on the third floor. It's labeled 'family' or something like that.
comment: Open nearly 24/7!

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
directions: in the back of store behind a door marked bathrooms.
comment: since the entrance to the bathrooms is behind a door, which bathroom you go in is private.

name: Safeway
directions: Back of store, on right side of the building (near produce/beer & wine).
comment: Disabled-accessible, single-stall, locking restroom.  Popular pee spot, so you might have to wait your turn outside.

name: LGBT Resource Center
directions: Located next to the International House and Voorhies Hall, across from Olson Hall
comment: Gender free, single user, locked door with fantastic art work

name: Le Petit Zinc
directions: In the corner of the dining room. Single stall genderfree. The building is 1 story and kind of inconspicuous.
comment: http://lepetitzincdetroit.com/

name: Goddard College
directions: As of this summer, there is a gender-free bathroom in every public building and dorm at the College.
comment: there are a coupled gendered bathrooms, because women,including some transwomen, have asked that multi-stall bathrooms, feel safer gendered. But the College has renovated bathrooms in every public building for single-use,and/or with locks to make gender-free bathrooms.

name: Avalon International Breads
directions: In the back of this small bakery. Single stall locking genderfree.
comment: 6a - 6p most days. The bread is awesome. (313) 832-0008 if you wanna double check hours.

name: Northern Arizona University Engineering building (Bldg. 69)
street: South San Francisco Street, Flagstaff, Arizona 86011
directions: The engineering building is on the south side of campus. It is building #69. The bathroom is on the first floor.
comment: The building is closed to non-engineering students/faculty at night.

name: Indianapolis International Airport
directions: Every set of restrooms in the terminal and parking garage includes a single-stall accessible 'family restroom' (located between the men's and women's room) which anyone may use.
comment: I did a dance of joy in the terminal when I saw they'd included this feature in our new airport!

name: Long Room
comment: It's a bar. It seems after about 9 they sometimes ID depending on how crowded it is. It's more than likely you can just go in and use it though. 2nd bathroom is labeled \"LADIES/MEN\" (first is labeled \"LADIES\")

name: Her Bar
directions: To your left
comment: This is a queer bar with a mainly womyn scene, but the bathrooms are labeled \"Butch\" and \"Femme\" and anyone is welcome to use whichever they like

name: Long Haul InfoShop
directions: In the back room. Wheelchair accessible
comment: Open Monday-Thursday 6-9PM and Saturday and Sunday 3-11PMlots of weird people haning out, the place is a book & zine library so plenty of reading material at hand.

name: Powell's Bookstore
comment: Ask for key at the front desk, every employee will hand it over, no questions asked.

name: Holidays Bar & Grill
directions: Out front, near the bar, next to the men's room there is a single-stall bathroom with the man/woman sign on it.
comment: Blueberry pancakes with real maple syrup!

name: Community Coffee House
directions: Towards back of shop, past the service area.
comment: 7AM-9PM every day. Corner of St. Philip and Royal, in the heart of the Quarter. Great coffee and pastries, nice staff.

name: Jax Brewery
directions: Two family restrooms on first floor.

name: Flagstaff Department of Motor Vehicles
directions: When you first walk in, there are gendered bathrooms, but around the corner to the left (near the waiting area) there is a single-stall unisex wheelchair-accessible toilet.
comment: Hours are Mon-Sat 8:00AM to 5:00PM; closed on Sat/Sun.

name: ASU East Hall
directions: 2nd floor. walk in main entrance, take first right and immediate right is stairwell. Go up to second floor then turn left. go to end of hall, turn left again and the bathroom is on the left.
comment: bathtub

name: Down to Earth
directions: Back of store near deli area.
comment: M-Su 7:30am - 10pm.  Enough people go in and out that you shouldn't have a problem just going in to pee, but being discreet can't hurt.  Single stall bathrooms (2) are disabled accessible and gender neutral.

name: Honolulu Chinatown Police Station
directions: Front of police substation.  Officer must buzz you in to use restroom.
comment: One gender neutral bathroom stall.  They didn't seem to mind anyone just coming in for the purpose of using the restroom.

name: starbucks across from congress square
directions: first floor, in the back
comment: two unisex bathrooms available for use w/o purchase!

name: SeQuential Biofuels
directions: Go into the convenience store and two large, clean, wheelchair accessible,gender neutral bathrooms are directly ahead of you.
comment: This place is right at an exit off the 5, just south of Eugene proper. It's lovely and open and a great place to stop if you're driving on the highway.

name: FreeGeek Chicago
directions: Open Fri 10-3 and Sun 11-5.In the basement of the Foot Locker building.  Entrance is around back, in the alley, near the convenience store entrance.
comment: We're a non-profit that provides low-cost computers, job training, and a community space for geeks.  People of all skill levels (from the lowest to the highest) volunteer here, all are welcome.  Dee is the trans staff member, but most of the staff are trans allies.

name: F. Futs and Company
directions: Coming in from the back and up the stairs, it's on the right behind a marked door. There are two single stall locking genderfree bathrooms; one is around the corner.Coming in from the main entrance, go past the stage and into the sandwich shop. It's on the left of the booths.
comment: This place has great local music often, and open mic night on Fridays at 7. Very cozy.

name: Cross Cultural Center
directions: located on the corner of Shields and East Quad, across from Olson Hall
comment: Two restrooms, both gender neutral, single user, with locks

name: Savers
directions: On the south wall, near the cashiers and entrance.
comment: **BONUS** Unisex changing stalls!!! Oh happy day.Hours: Mon - Sat 9-9, Sun 10-7

name: University of Colorado at Boulder
directions: Walk in West doors of Engineering building and it's to the left in the commons area.

name: Performing Arts Garage
directions: In ground floor of garage on corner nearest to Grove & Gough.
comment: Garage open 6 am to Midnight weekdays, open for special events on weekends.

name: Panama Hotel cafe
directions: one non-gendered bathroom downstairs, single occupancy, locking, not accessible

name: Japan Inn
comment: You have to be a patron. There are two separate women's bathrooms and one men's.
